.TH man 1 "24 May 2023" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
- C-based interactive shell for Linux operating systems.

.SH SYNOPSIS
 hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
A shell, also known as a command interpreter, is the user interface for interacting with an operating system. It processes and executes the commands entered by the user. The shell provides a command syntax and acts as a programming layer in the system.

.B Overview

The simple shell is a command-line tool that reads and interprets lines of input from either a file or the terminal. It executes various commands and is launched when a user logs into the system. It offers interactive features and supports both interactive use and non-interactive use through shell scripts. Commands can be entered directly in the running simple shell or stored in a file and executed by the shell.

.SH Return Value

A return value of 0 indicates success, while any other number indicates failure.

.SH PATH

The simple shell searches for executables in all directories specified in the PATH environment variable.

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Additional command options can be appended to the main command, separated by a space and a '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLE

[command] [options]
$ ls -l

.SH BUGS
A single space must be provided after each argument.


.SH AUTHOR
Hussein A. Wario, Naftal Osoro.
